author: stsp
msg: Make 'svn patch' a little bit stricter when checking for added files.
(patch_target_t): Make docstring imply that a patch needs to create
a non-empty file for us to consider it for addition.
(resolve_target_path): It's way to early here to make any assumptions
about what the patch will do. Leave TARGET->ADDED alone.
(apply_one_patch: If the patch did create a non-empty file for a target
which did not exist prior to patching, the patch has added a file.
